{"chapter_summary": "This chapter describes the primordial creation by Brahman (Svayambhu). Through tapas (austerity), Brahman first creates Sveda (sweat-born being), then from sweat-drops creates waters (apas), from which Bhrigu is born. Bhrigu is named Atharvan, who becomes Prajapati. From Atharvan, ten groups of Atharvana rishis and the Atharvana Veda are produced. Then Brahman creates the three worlds, three gods (Agni, Vayu, Aditya), three Vedas (Rg, Yajur, Sama), and three great utterances (bhur, bhuva, svar). From the waters that became the ocean, Varuna (death) arises, and from him Angiras is born, leading to the Angirasa Veda. Finally, Brahman creates five additional Vedas (Sarpa, Pisaca, Asura, Itihasa, Purana) and performs the first sacrifice with gods as priests.", "entities": [{"name": "Brahman (Svayambhu)", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Svayambhu", "Brahma"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.1", "gopa_1.1.2", "gopa_1.1.3", "gopa_1.1.4", "gopa_1.1.5", "gopa_1.1.6", "gopa_1.1.7", "gopa_1.1.8", "gopa_1.1.9", "gopa_1.1.10", "gopa_1.1.11", "gopa_1.1.12", "gopa_1.1.13"]}, {"name": "Sveda", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Sveda"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.1"]}, {"name": "Bhrigu", "kind": "sage", "aliases": ["Atharvan", "Prajapati"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.3", "gopa_1.1.4"]}, {"name": "Atharvan", "kind": "sage", "aliases": ["Bhrigu", "Prajapati"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.4", "gopa_1.1.5"]}, {"name": "Prajapati", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Atharvan", "Bhrigu"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.4", "gopa_1.1.13"]}, {"name": "Agni", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.6", "gopa_1.1.13"]}, {"name": "Vayu", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.6", "gopa_1.1.13"]}, {"name": "Aditya", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Surya"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.6", "gopa_1.1.13"]}, {"name": "Varuna", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Mrtyu"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.7"]}, {"name": "Mrtyu", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Varuna"], "verse_r