{"chapter_summary": "This chapter from the Gopatha Brahmana explores the nature of Savitri (the Gayatri mantra) as the union of pairs (mithuna) such as mind-speech, fire-earth, etc. It describes how the brahmacarin (celibate student) embodies cosmic principles through discipline, and includes a dialogue between King Janamejaya and the fires Dakshinagni and Ahavaniya, emphasizing brahmacarya as the highest virtue.", "entities": [{"name": "Savitri", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Gayatri"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33", "gopa_1.1.34", "gopa_1.1.35", "gopa_1.1.36", "gopa_1.1.37", "gopa_1.1.38"]}, {"name": "Savitā", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Savitar"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33", "gopa_1.1.34"]}, {"name": "Agni", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33", "gopa_1.2.3", "gopa_1.2.4", "gopa_1.2.6"]}, {"name": "Vāyu", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33", "gopa_1.2.1"]}, {"name": "Āditya", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Surya"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33", "gopa_1.2.1"]}, {"name": "Candramā", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Moon"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33"]}, {"name": "Pṛthivī", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Earth"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33"]}, {"name": "Antarikṣa", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["atmosphere"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33"]}, {"name": "Dyauḥ", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["Heaven"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.1.33"]}, {"name": "Brahmacārī", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["celibate student"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.2.1", "gopa_1.2.2", "gopa_1.2.3", "gopa_1.2.4", "gopa_1.2.5", "gopa_1.2.6", "gopa_1.2.7"]}, {"name": "Janamejaya", "kind": "king", "aliases": ["Pārīkṣita"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.2.5"]}, {"name": "Dakṣiṇāgni", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["southern fire"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.2.5"]}, {"name": "Āhavanīya", "kind": "deity", "aliases": ["offering fire"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.2.5"]}, {"name": "Dantāvala Dhaumra", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.