{"chapter_summary": "This chapter of the Gopatha Brahmana discusses the Agnihotra ritual, its deities, the distribution of sacrificial portions, and the consequences of improper performance. It includes dialogues between sages, explanations of cosmic correspondences, and the importance of knowledge in ritual.", "entities": [{"name": "Indra", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.5"]}, {"name": "Uddālaka Āruṇi", "kind": "sage", "aliases": ["Gautama"], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.6", "gopa_1.3.7", "gopa_1.3.8", "gopa_1.3.11", "gopa_1.3.12"]}, {"name": "Svaidāyana Śaunaka", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.6", "gopa_1.3.8"]}, {"name": "Prācīnayogya", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.11", "gopa_1.3.13"]}, {"name": "Prajāpati", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.15"]}, {"name": "Agni", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.15", "gopa_1.3.16"]}, {"name": "Sūrya", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.15"]}, {"name": "Anumati", "kind": "deity", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.15"]}, {"name": "Svāhā", "kind": "concept", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.16"]}, {"name": "Kārava ṛṣis", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.17"]}, {"name": "Priyamedhas Bharadvājas", "kind": "sage", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.15"]}, {"name": "Yajña", "kind": "concept", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.20"]}], "relationships": [{"src": "Uddālaka Āruṇi", "rel": "teacher_of", "dst": "Prācīnayogya", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.11", "gopa_1.3.12", "gopa_1.3.13"]}, {"src": "Svaidāyana Śaunaka", "rel": "student_of", "dst": "Uddālaka Āruṇi", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.6", "gopa_1.3.8"]}, {"src": "Indra", "rel": "took", "dst": "ukthāni sāmāni", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.5"]}], "story": {"title": "The Agnihotra and Its Mysteries", "arc": "Exposition of ritual knowledge and its cosmic significance", "characters": ["Uddālaka Āruṇi", "Svaidāyana Śaunaka", "Prācīnayogya", "Priyamedhas Bharadvājas", "Kārava ṛṣis"], "timeline_note": "Mythical time, dialogues between sages", "comic_potential": "The Priyamedhas' disagreement on how many times to perform Agnihotra and the subsequent success of the one who performed it twice."}, "teachings": [{"teaching": "The Agnihotra ritual should be performed twice, with both mantra and mind.", "lens_note": "Sharma's Kriya-Yoga: This emphasizes the integration of external action (yajus) and internal concentration (manas), aligning with the principle of harmonizing body and mind in practice.", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.15"]}, {"teaching": "Knowledge of the ritual's meaning is essential; otherwise, the ritual is ineffective.", "lens_note": "Sharma's Kriya-Yoga: Highlights the importance of jnana (knowledge) in kriya (action). Mere mechanical performance without understanding yields no fruit.", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.13", "gopa_1.3.14"]}, {"teaching": "The universe is a macrocosm of the sacrificial altar; the body is a microcosm.", "lens_note": "Sharma's Kriya-Yoga: This reflects the principle of correspondence between the individual and the cosmos, a key concept in Kriya-Yoga where the body is seen as a temple.", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.9", "gopa_1.3.10"]}, {"teaching": "Svāhā is the essence of the sacrifice, born of truth, and its deity is Agni.", "lens_note": "Sharma's Kriya-Yoga: Svāhā represents the offering of the self, the inner fire of transformation. Agni as deity symbolizes the inner fire of purification.", "verse_ranges": ["gopa_1.3.16"]}], "_provenance": {"purana": "Gopatha Brahmana", "chapter_label": "Chapter 0 (part 5)", "seq_start": 321, "seq_end": 335, "chunk_ids": ["gopatha-0-321", "gopatha-0-322", "gopatha-0-323", "gopatha-0-324", "gopatha-0-325", "gopatha-0-326", "gopatha-0-327", "gopatha-0-328", "gopatha-0-329", "gopatha-0-330", "gopatha-0-331", "gopatha-0-332", "gopatha-0-333", "gopatha-0-334", "gopatha-0-335"], "prov